        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 5 at 6:41AM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>Light snow has moved into Fergus County this morning. This snow
will continue through at the next few hours. The snow is reducing
visibility to one mile or less. Little to no snow accumulation is
expected on roadways.

If traveling be prepared for changing conditions, make sure your
headlights are on, slow down, and use caution.
</description>
